<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 26 Jan 2009
Source: OIE WAHID animal disease interface Weekly Disease Information
Vol. 22 - No. 05, January 2009 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=7724>


Information received on 26 Jan 2009 from Mr Spirus Doudounakis, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Director General, Directorate General of
Veterinary Services, Ministry of Rural Development and Food, Athens,
Greece

Summary

Report type: Follow-up report No. 2
Start date: 3 Nov 2008
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 5 Nov 2008
Report date: 26 Jan 2009
Date submitted to OIE: 26 Jan 2009
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2001
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 16
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports Immediate notification (7 Nov 2008)
Follow-up report No. 1 (19 Jan 2009)
Follow-up report No. 2 (26 Jan 2009)

New outbreaks:

[30 "new outbreaks" are covered in this follow-up report (which we
have abridged), all in sheep on the Greek island of Lesvos. Their
respective start dates were between 6 and 23 Nov 2008. According to
this report, no cattle or goats in the affected farms have been
clinically affected. Locations of the outbreaks are given by place
numbers (e.g. Lesvos 14, Lesvos 15, etc.) and not by village names;
all are reportedly in the administrative region "Voreio Aigaio"
(several north Aegean Islands, of which Lesvos is the largest). For
the start date and the number of susceptible animals, cases, deaths
etc. in each outbreak, interested subscribers are referred to the
above URL, which includes also a map with all outbreaks marked. -
Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 30
